AB  - A general equilibrium two-country two-good two-currency model with stochastic production and money supply is set up. Money is introduced via a cash-in-advance constraint. The timing of information and transactions is such that a combined transactions, precautionary and storeof-value demand results, with variable income velocity of money. The equilibrium is solved explicity. Effects of temporary and permanent disturbances in the supply of currencies are examined, in particular the effects on the terms-of-trade, nominal and real interest rates, and on real asset prices in general. Monetary policy has real effects.
