AB  - This paper examines a small open economy with endogenous employment using an intergenerational model. Under floating rates, risk-averse workers enhance their welfare through currency substitution. Workers' currency substitution behavior produces a Phillips curve with anticipated exchange rate movement and domestic inflationary expectation as explanatory variables. The dependence of the level of equilibrium employment on the terms of trade is demonstrated. Finally, the association between exchange rates and current accounts is examined in relation to the role of money.
